File: Eskom Chief Operating Officer Jan Oberholzer. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom COO Jan Oberholzer has been cleared of all wrongdoing in a payment dispute with contractor Aveng.
An investigation was launched after an employee lodged a grievance. READ: Electricity Crisis: Government opens IPP door The Eskom board says it condemns the unfounded allegations, which brings the company into disrepute. It says it has confidence in its COO and will continue to give him support.